node.text:
The LAPD has reportedly instructed its officers to collect social media information on every civilian they stop, even if they haven't been arrested or accused of a crime, according to documents obtained by the Brennan Center for Justice.

BCJ claims to have reviewed 10 sets of documents obtained through a request to the LAPD under the California Public Records Act, which it says reveal the department's diverse mass surveillance tactics, including collecting social media information during interviews. The nonprofit organization says the procedure raises concerns about the department infringing on the civil liberties of civilians without a warrant.

According to the Guardian, with whom BCJ shared the documents, LAPD officers utilize 'field interview cards,' which include space for them to record social media account information on any civilian they speak to. According to the Guardian, police chief Michel Moore allegedly told officers and their supervisors that it ‘was critical to collect the data for use in ‘investigations, arrests, and prosecutions,’ and warned that supervisors would review cards to ensure they were complete.’

'There are real dangers about police having all of this social media identifying information at their fingertips,' said Rachel Levinson-Waldman, a deputy director at BCJ, to the Guardian.

'There is a long history of law enforcement using surveillance, whether in-person or through digital technologies to attack Black and Latino movements fighting for racial justice,' added Jacinta González, an organizer with advocacy group Mijente.

#losangeles #lapd #socialmedia #justice

node.text:
Sen. Amy Klobuchar shared her breast cancer diagnosis in a blog post on Thursday. The senator from Minnesota wrote that doctors found ‘calcifications’ during a routine mammogram in February. A biopsy showed that they were signs of Stage 1A breast cancer. Klobuchar says that she had a lumpectomy and radiation treatment and that the treatment ‘went well,’ adding that doctors think her ‘chances of developing cancer again are no greater than the average person.’⁠
⁠
Klobuchar used the announcement to remind people of the importance of physicals and routine examinations. ‘I delayed mine [because of the pandemic],’ Klobuchar warned. She continued, ‘It’s easy to put off health screenings, just like I did. But I hope my experience is a reminder for everyone of the value of routine health checkups, exams, and follow-through.’⁠
⁠
⁠
#health #breastcancer #mammograms #breastcancerawareness #amyklobuchar

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by NowThis Politics on September 09, 2021. May be an image of one or more people, outdoors, monument and text that says '2 victims of the 9/11 WTC attacks are identified 20 years later NOW THIS S hay MRMRECAN via IOHN News China Pan'.

node.text:
Just days before the 20th anniversary of 9/11, the New York City Office of the Chief Medical Examiner says it has identified 2 more victims of the World Trade Center attacks that killed 2,753 people almost 20 years ago, per NBC News.⁠
⁠
According to officials, DNA analysis revealed the identity of Dorothy Morgan of Hempstead, NY. DNA analysis also identified a man, whose family requested that his name stay anonymous. They are the 1,646th and 1,647th people to be identified as victims of the attacks on the WTC.⁠
⁠
'When they told me that there were remains found, it was a shock,’ said Dorothy's daughter, Nykiah Morgan, to NBC New York. Morgan continued, 'It's like you're living it all over again.'⁠
⁠
'Twenty years ago, we made a promise to the families of World Trade Center victims to do whatever it takes for as long as it takes to identify their loved ones, and with these two new identifications, we continue to fulfill that sacred obligation,' said Dr. Barbara A. Sampson, the chief medical examiner, in a statement. 'No matter how much time passes since September 11, 2001, we will never forget, and we pledge to use all the tools at our disposal to make sure all those who were lost can be reunited with their families.’⁠
⁠
According to officials, about 40% of the victims, or 1,100+ people, remain unidentified.⁠
⁠
⁠
#911 #nineeleven #wtc #forensics

node.text:
Former President Donald Trump repeatedly praised Gen. Robert E. Lee in a statement decrying the removal of a statue of the Confederate leader in Richmond, Virginia, a statue Trump called ‘magnificent’ and ‘beautiful.’⁠
⁠
‘He should be remembered as perhaps the greatest unifying force after the war was over,’ Trump said of Lee, who commanded the losing army in a war that resulted in the most American deaths of any war in history.⁠
⁠
Trump also said that Lee would’ve delivered a ‘total victory’ in Afghanistan had he been alive today. Trump failed to mention that his administration had negotiated many of the elements of the U.S.’s withdrawal from the country.⁠
⁠
⁠
#formerpresidentdonaldtrump #news #politics #virginia #statue
